SCALABILITY ANALYSIS
Juniper Mist WLAN Best Practices Automation Script
Scenario: 2,000 sites  |  100,000 WLAN clients  |  Self-imposed limit: 2,000 API calls/hr  |  Mist platform limit: 5,000 API calls/hr
Version 2.0.0  —  April 2026

 
1. Purpose
This document describes how the Mist WLAN Best Practices Automation script behaves at scale. It quantifies exactly how many Mist API calls the script makes during a complete run, identifies where the self-imposed rate limit of 2,000 calls per hour is likely to be reached, explains the impact on total runtime, and recommends the safest way to adjust the limit for large organisations.
2. API Rate Limits
The Mist platform allows each API token up to 5,000 API calls per rolling 60-minute window. The script deliberately sets a lower self-imposed ceiling of 2,000 calls per hour, leaving a 3,000-call safety margin. When the script approaches the ceiling (within 50 calls of the limit), it pauses automatically and waits for the window to reset before continuing.
Limit	Value	Source
Mist platform hard limit	5,000 calls / hr	Juniper Mist API documentation
Script self-imposed ceiling	2,000 calls / hr	Configured in script (API_RATE_LIMIT)
Safety buffer	50 calls	Configured in script (RATE_LIMIT_BUFFER)
Guard triggers at	1,950 calls	2,000 − 50
Safety headroom vs. Mist	3,000 calls / hr	5,000 − 2,000
3. API Call Breakdown — 2,000 Sites
The table below shows every API call the script makes during a full run against an organisation with 2,000 sites. The number of calls is calculated using the actual pagination logic in the script (100 records per page).
Script Function	API Endpoint	Calls (2,000 sites)	Notes
verify_auth()	GET /self	1	One-time authentication check
get_sites()	GET /orgs/{id}/sites	20	2,000 sites ÷ 100 per page
get_org_wlans()	GET /orgs/{id}/wlans	1 – 5	Depends on WLAN count; 50 WLANs = 1 call
get_site_client_count()	GET /sites/{id}/stats/clients	2,000	⚠  1 call per site — primary bottleneck
get_all_sites_sle() 24h	GET /orgs/{id}/insights/sites-sle	20	2,000 sites ÷ 100 per page (efficient)
apply_best_practices()	PUT /orgs/{id}/wlans/{id}	0 – N	1 call per WLAN remediated; typically 1–20
collect_clients_after()	GET /sites/{id}/stats/clients	2,000	Re-fetched during post-change verification
get_all_sites_sle() 1h	GET /orgs/{id}/insights/sites-sle	20	Post-change SLE check

The single largest consumer of API calls is the per-site client count function. It must call the Mist API once per site, so an organisation with 2,000 sites requires exactly 2,000 API calls just for this one step — matching the entire self-imposed hourly limit before any other work is done. This function is called twice per full run (before and after changes), bringing the client-count subtotal alone to 4,000 calls.
