Key finding: With a self-imposed limit of 2,000 calls/hr and 2,000 sites, a full run takes approximately 2.2 hours — with roughly 100 minutes spent waiting for the rate limit window to reset rather than doing useful work.
6. Impact of 100,000 WLAN Clients
The number of connected wireless clients (100,000 in this scenario) does not increase the number of API calls the script makes. The client count endpoint returns a list of all connected clients at a site in a single response — the call count is determined by the number of sites (2,000), not the number of clients.
The impact of 100,000 clients is limited to:
•	Larger response payloads per site API call, which may slightly increase average response time (typically less than 0.1 second per call at this scale).
•	Higher memory usage while the client list is held in memory for counting. At 100,000 clients this is negligible — typically a few megabytes.
•	The client count figures displayed in the summary and Excel report will reflect the full 100,000 total, spread across the 2,000 sites.
